This paper deals with data management systems and optimization techniques, which are primarily related to the field of database systems (cs.DB). The use of a genetic algorithm for finding an optimal solution also suggests a connection to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of simulation and prediction, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on system scalability and performance optimization suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of a formal model and optimization problem suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
